  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_6' aria-label=\" Devinder Kumar Bansal versus The State of Punjab pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('6','2025','2025_3_1531_1546','2025INSC320'); ><font size='4'> <strong>DEVINDER KUMAR BANSAL<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF PUNJAB </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 3 S.C.R. 1531</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 320</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006902025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether the High Court justified in denying anticipatory bail to the petitioner in connection with FIR registered against the petitioner for the offence punishable u/s.7 of the 1988 Act and s.61(2) of the BNS 2023. Headnotes&dagger; Prevention of Corruption Act, s.61(2) &ndash; Illegal gratification &ndash; Anticipatory bail &ndash; Denial &ndash; Petitioner-Audit Inspector with the Government demanded illegal gratification in connection with conducting of audit during the tenure of complainant&rsquo;s wife as Sarpanch of Gram Panchayat &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 03-03-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CRIMINAL) No. 3247/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('6','2025','2025_3_1531_1546','2025INSC320','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('6','2025','202